# Architecture design (phase 2)

Part of [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc). **Every feature change** that requires feature analysis also requires architecture design. **No production or test code** until phases 1–4 are complete.

Canonical references: [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md), [docs/adr/](../../docs/adr/), [adr.mdc](adr.mdc), [contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc](contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc), [contraponto-bounded-contexts.mdc](contraponto-bounded-contexts.mdc).

## When required

Any change that triggers feature analysis ([change-request-analysis.mdc](change-request-analysis.mdc)) — **mandatory**. Docs-only exempt with feature analysis.

## Preconditions

- Phase 1 exit criteria met.
- Blocking **FQ*n*** are `answered` or `not valid`.

## Process

### 1. Apply baseline ADRs

Confirm design complies with Accepted ADRs [0001–0005](../../docs/adr/README.md). Do not contradict without a new ADR.

### 2. Create or update ADRs for transversal decisions

Per [adr.mdc](adr.mdc): new ADR → `Proposed`; edit `Accepted` only after user **reopens** with justification.

### 3. Add or extend `## Architecture` on the feature doc

| Area | Document |
|------|----------|
| **ADRs aplicáveis** | Links to relevant Accepted ADRs |
| Bounded contexts | Contexts involved; dependency direction |
| Packages / layers | Endpoint → Service → Repository per operation |
| Routes / templates | `@Path`, Qute templates, HTMX targets, `*Paths` builders |
| Schema / persistence | Tables, Flyway migration file(s) |
| Cross-context integration | CDI events ([cdi-events.md](../../docs/cdi-events.md)) |
| Presentation | Qute fragments, `components/`, CSS bundle (main/manage/write) |
| Tests | `@WebTest` + `App`/`Given`, unit, ArchUnit |

Revise when **AQ*n*** or footprint-changing **FQ*n*** answers change design.

### 4. Track architecture questions (AQ*n*)

**When answered:** impact review; transversal → ADR; local → feature **Architecture** only.

### 5. Validate against architecture rules

1. [contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc](contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc)
2. [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) bounded contexts
3. [contraponto-core.mdc](contraponto-core.mdc) — URLs via `*Paths`, not hardcoded templates
4. [htmx-events.md](../../docs/htmx-events.md) — scoped refresh, auth allowlist
5. Flyway — incremental `db/migration/V*.sql` (never rewrite applied migrations)
6. ADRs — no conflict with Accepted decisions

### 6. Set status and stop

Set changelog **Status:** `architecture-ready`. Present **Architecture**, ADRs, open **AQ*n***. **Stop** until blocking AQ resolved.

## Exit criteria

- Relevant ADRs linked; no new ADR in `Accepted` without manual user acceptance.
- `## Architecture` complete.
- Blocking **AQ*n*** resolved.
- Status `architecture-ready`. **No code.**
